description:
A 2.5 stars review;
5 stars for food and 0 star for their judgmental service.
Woke up from a super fun party a night before, I stumbled there, hoping to get some nice Italian brekkie. The staff who was taking care of my brekkie shot a from-head-to-toe judging look at my beige jeans and my tshirt, which is fine. I ended up ordering some eggs, bacons, and sausages brekkie with a decaf coffee and never got a refill for water or coffee. The guy walked to a table of middle-aged Caucasian couple behind me and kept checking in with them if they would need anymore coffee or juice or whatever but never cared enough to hear my "Excuse me!"s. Well, at least he was pretty quick in shoving the check in my face right after I put away my utensils, but still didn't care enough to fill my water glass nor my coffee cup up. I ain't sure if its because of my too casual clothes or me being Asian with no name brand stuff on that made a big difference on a service between the table behind me and my table. Well, at least my eggs were sunny side up, just like I asked for. What else would I be able to ask for from a brekkie place other than the quality of food, right?
